  "text": "where G is the collective health detriment, which was assumed to be proportional to the EDE; and R k is the radiation risk factor given as 5 × 10 −2 Sv −1 (ICRP, 2007) . This value represents the number of individuals with cancer-related health issues. The risk of incurring a cancer due to the controlled releases of (the selected) radioisotopes in the four cities is small compared to the cancer risk associated with terrestrial gamma radiation in some other cities [CITATION_1] with the same geological formations as the ones considered by the current work.",
